# Mobile UI Architecture

## Structure
- Organize by feature modules.
- Screens stay thin; delegate logic to hooks/services.
- Shared UI elements live in a shared components folder.

## Components
- Reusable and platform-friendly.
- Avoid large screen components; split into smaller UI blocks.

## State
- Local UI state in screens/components.
- Shared app state uses a global store.

## Data Fetching
- API calls in services; screens should not fetch directly.

## Performance & Maintainability
- Minimize re-renders, lazy-load heavy screens.
- Extract repeated UI into reusable components.

## Deprecated Safety
- Never introduce deprecated APIs or components.
- Replace outdated code with recommended alternatives.
